---

NAME
    gotty - Share your terminal as a web application

SYNOPSIS
    gotty [options] <command> [<arguments...>]

DESCRIPTION
    GoTTY is a simple command line tool that turns your CLI tools into web applications. It starts a web server that creates a browser-based terminal, allowing remote access to your local terminal session.

OPTIONS
    --address, -a           IP address to listen on (default: "0.0.0.0")
    --port, -p              Port number to listen on (default: "8080")
    --permit-write, -w      Permit clients to write to the TTY (default: false)
    --credential, -c        Credential for Basic Authentication (ex: user:pass)
    --random-url, -r        Add a random string to the URL (default: false)
    --random-url-length     Random URL length (default: 8)
    --tls, -t               Enable TLS/SSL (default: false)
    --tls-crt               TLS/SSL certificate file path
    --tls-key               TLS/SSL key file path
    --index                 Custom index.html file
    --title-format          Title format of browser window
    --reconnect             Enable reconnection (default: false)
    --reconnect-time        Time to reconnect (default: 10)
    --once                  Accept only one client and exit on disconnection
    --permit-arguments      Permit clients to send arguments to command
    --width                 Static width of the terminal
    --height                Static height of the terminal
    --ws-origin             A regular expression that matches origin URLs to allow websocket access from
    --term                  Terminal name to use on the browser side
    -v, --version           Print the version

USAGE
    gotty [options] <command> [<arguments...>]

EXAMPLES
    gotty top
    gotty -w bash
    gotty -p 8080 -w ssh user@host

OUTPUT
    GoTTY starts a web server and provides a URL to access the terminal session.
